description._content: Description: New sea front road being made at Baie St. Anne, Praslin. The work proceeds rather slowly, as, for once, stones are not easy to find. Location: Praslin, Seychelles Date: 1900-1929 Description: Quarters at Baie St. Anne, of J.P. Praslin District. House of 6 rooms, back and front verandas, pantry, usual outhouses, and good bath room. Built in 1901. Location: Praslin, Seychelles Date: 1901 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/771 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
